=== T009: chunk-url-grammar.md path-segment grammar consistent with manifest schema's path regex ===
--- Schema path regex (sqlite_pages_entry) ---
^(?!/)(?!.*\.\.)([A-Za-z0-9_.\-]+)(/[A-Za-z0-9_.\-]+)*$
--- Schema path regex (whole_file_entry) ---
^(?!/)(?!.*\.\.)([A-Za-z0-9_.\-]+)(/[A-Za-z0-9_.\-]+)*$
--- Cross-check: same pattern on both entry kinds? ---
OK: identical path regex on both entry shapes
--- chunk-url-grammar.md prohibitions and component-character grammar ---
47:- `<path>` is the manifest entry's `path` value verbatim, with each path component URL-encoded per RFC 3986 §2 (forward slashes between components are NOT encoded). The schema's path pattern restricts components to `[A-Za-z0-9_.-]`, so URL-encoding is normally a no-op.
75:- **No URL-encoded segment traversal.** The schema's `path` pattern rejects `..` segments; the grammar inherits that restriction. URLs constructed under this grammar refer only to under-canonical-prefix paths.
